{
  "texts": [
    "'LLM-as-a-Judge', which refers to an LLM tasked with evaluating, scoring, or assessing the quality, correctness, or appropriateness of outputs, has recently been described 55 and its applicability has been discussed 56.",
    "Utilising the capabilities of LLMs for initial screening can significantly reduce the time and resource demands on human evaluators.",
    "This can make the CREOLA framework more scalable and efficient over time.",
    "This hybrid approach aligns with ongoing advancements in AI and has the potential to maintain rigorous oversight while ensuring scalability.",
    "In this work, we present a framework for the clinical safety assessment of LLMs in clinical documentation scenarios."
  ]
}